      "span_text": "Emulsions showed a reduced droplet size with increasing homogenization pressure (HP) used during their preparation (Table 1) , which was as observed in many previous studies [CITATION_1] , and no significant difference in droplet size of emulsions stabilized by whey protein isolate (WPI), sodium caseinate (SCN) and Tween ® 80 (TW80), processed at similar homogenization pressures, was observed."
